stylometry: This allows you to run the same simulation several times at the same time using a different value each time.  You would use this in a simulation model when you have different quantities and you want to see which one has the highest mean profit.  For example, if you owned a book store and you want to know how many of each book to hold (20,30,40,50,or 60) you can run this RISKIMTABLE to figure out how many of each book to keep in your inventory.  The way this works is the risk analysis runs several different tests (5 in this case) with random demands.  This conclusion allows you do make the decision with each demand how many books you should keep in your inventory to minimize the supply but at the same time supply the demand.
